Web parity gap map

Home
├─ stats + recent courses          mobile: partial
├─ course generation feedback      mobile: partial
└─ "view all" flow                 mobile: missing wiring

Courses
├─ progress-based filtering        mobile: missing
├─ offline indicator/sync cues     mobile: missing
└─ archive action                  mobile: missing UI

Course detail / learning
├─ rich generation progress        mobile: partial
├─ continue/resume generation      mobile: missing
└─ better lesson-generation state  mobile: partial

Settings
├─ real theme system               mobile: missing
├─ AI provider settings            mobile: missing
└─ settings persistence/testing    mobile: missing

Offline / platform
├─ per-course offline cache        mobile: missing
├─ explicit offline UX             mobile: missing
└─ notifications / sync            mobile: missing


Settings parity first
Reason: the web app already treats AI configuration as a first-class feature, and mobile currently exposes a settings screen that looks real but is mostly fake. That creates trust debt fastest.

Generation progress + continue/resume second
Reason: this is the core differentiated flow. If mobile can generate but users cannot clearly monitor or recover generation, the product feels unreliable.

Courses list parity third
Reason: progress-based filtering is high-frequency behavior and aligns mobile with the web mental model better than the current archived tab setup.

Offline course-detail caching fourth
Reason: this becomes much more valuable once people are actually using generated courses on mobile. It is also a bigger behavior investment than the UI gaps above.

Home polish fifth
Reason: useful, but lower leverage than settings and generation recovery.